It would be awesome to optimize `custom_code`. Sometimes it works slowly.

Current implementation:
```python
def custom_code(mask: str = '@###',
                char: str = '@', digit: str = '#') -> str:
    code = ''
    for p in mask:
        if p == char:
            code += choice(string.ascii_uppercase)
        elif p == digit:
            code += str(randint(0, 9))
        else:
            code += p
    return code
```

Hello, I've been able to implement FileSaver.js without issue. Works great, but I'm curious about something. I've been using it with input fields that dynamically update divs in a separate container on the page. Everything works, but I'm curious if it is possible to require the inputs be completed before the prepared file is available for download. 

I'm thinking something along the lines of: 

if($('input.required') === "" || $('input.required') === "placeholder"){
    // console alert box prompted
}else{
    // proceed with prepare and save. 
}

I've done some digging through the files and have yet to recognize how to do this if possible. Any input would be appreciated.

the way it is now:

st-sort="calc.somefunctionname"

The down side of this is that you are the only one that can pass anything to this function and right now you're only passing the row value.  If you are looping through some headers you might want to be able to pass some secondary information in order to complete the sorting calculation like the $index of what you're looping on.

The upside for you or doing it the the way you have it right now is that what you do var getter = $parse(stSortAttributeValue) you can check to see if it's a function by doing angular.isFunction(getter(scope)) more easily.

What I want to be able to do is declare it the way angular lets you on other attributes i.e.

st-sort="calc.somefunctionname(val,$index)"

This way I have more control over what's being passed to this function. The downside for you is that you wouldn't be able to do angular.isFunction(getter(scope)) to see if it's a function anymore because it would call the function. I've build other directives in the past and although it might seem kinda jank you could just do this to check to see if the attribute string is a function _.contains(theAttribute,'(') && _.contains(theAttribute,')')

here's an example how how I did something similar:

```
							var field = $(this).attr('st-export'),
								getter = $parse(field),
								v;

                            // in this case field is something like mySortFunction($row)
							if(_.contains(field,'(') && _.contains(field,')')) {
                                // if it's a function than execute it on the scope and pass the current row
								v = getter(scope,{
									$row : row
								});
							} else {
                                // if it's just some dot notation like myfield.total than just get the value of that in the context of the row
								v = getter(row);
							}
                            return v;
```

Please, replace this code
```
def anonymous_user_required(f):
    @wraps(f)
    def wrapper(*args, **kwargs):
        if current_user.is_authenticated:
            return redirect(utils.get_url(_security.post_login_view))
        return f(*args, **kwargs)
    return wrapper
```
with 
```
def anonymous_user_required(f):
    @wraps(f)
    def wrapper(*args, **kwargs):
        if current_user.is_authenticated():
            return redirect(utils.get_url(_security.post_login_view))
        return f(*args, **kwargs)
    return wrapper
```
Note that the missing braces are a big problem because the PROPERTY current_user.is_authenticated is ALWAYS True, whereas the FUNCTION is_authenticated is not.

