I propose to change the design of the dataflow to be more concise when using the python idiomatic variant of:

```python
class MyFlow(DataFlow):
   def __init__(self, ...):
   def __iter__(self, ...):
   def __len__(self, ....): 
```

This would make the code somewhat more consistent to other python objects:

```python
class SomeData(object):
  def __init__(self, start, len=10):
    super(SomeData, self).__init__()
    self.start = start
    self.len = len

  def __len__(self):
    return self.len

  def __iter__(self):
    for i in range(self.start, self.start + self.len):
      yield [i]


class AddOne(object):
  """docstring for AddOne"""

  def __init__(self, other_ds):
    super(AddOne, self).__init__()
    self.other_ds = other_ds

  def __len__(self):
    return len(self.other_ds)

  def __iter__(self):
    for i in self.other_ds:
      yield [i[0] + 1]


ds = SomeData(2, 3)
ds = AddOne(ds)
for dp in ds:
  print(dp)
```

In fact, all `dataflow.*`  objects are just glorified [container types](https://docs.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html#emulating-container-types) (ok most of them). So why not using the python terminology then? To keep backward compatibility, the `get_data()` and `size()` can wrap the `__iter__` and `__len__`. I would advise against using `__next__` to not bloating the code.

I could do a pass and apply the changes accordingly, but I am not eager to open yet another PR -- and even more so when not discussed beforehand.

Maybe even `__str__` can take over the implementation of `PrintData`. I see currently no usage of PrintData outside debugging.

```python
ds = SomeData(2, 3)
print(ds)
```

seems a better fit and more descriptive than

```python
ds = SomeData(2, 3)
ds = PrintData(ds)
next(ds.get_data())
```

The only problem I can see is when using `PrintData` at multiple places. But again, `PrintData` shouldn't be deprecated. Instead `__str__` can be an additional feature. Or even better, `print(ds)` can print the entire dataflow information of all stacked dataflow mappings.
